  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the best poems in Hindi for mothers?",
  "response": "Hindi poetry has a rich tradition of expressing love, gratitude, and reverence for mothers. Here are some of the best and most celebrated Hindi poems dedicated to mothers:\n\n---\n\n### **1. \"Maa\" by Harivansh Rai Bachchan**\n(From the collection \"Madhushala\")  \nThis heartfelt poem captures the selfless love and sacrifices of a mother. It reflects on how a mother\u2019s love is boundless and unconditional.\n\n---\n\n### **2. \"Maa Ka Aashirwad\" by Maithili Sharan Gupt**\nThis poem beautifully portrays a mother\u2019s blessings as the foundation of a child\u2019s life. It emphasizes the emotional and spiritual strength a mother provides.\n\n---\n\n### **3. \"Maa Ek Kavita\" by Ramdhari Singh 'Dinkar'**\nDinkar\u2019s poem is a tribute to the nurturing and protective nature of a mother. It highlights the mother as the first teacher and the greatest source of inspiration.\n\n---\n\n### **4. \"Maa Tujhe Salaam\" by Gulzar**\nAn emotional and lyrical poem, Gulzar captures the essence of a mother\u2019s love and the deep bond between a mother and child. It is often celebrated for its simplicity and depth.\n\n---\n\n### **5. \"Maa\" by Jaishankar Prasad**\nThis poem from the collection \"Kamayani\" reflects on the divine and sacred relationship between a mother and her child. It portrays the mother as the embodiment of purity and compassion.\n\n---\n\n### **6. \"Mera Bachpan\" by Mahadevi Verma**\nWhile not exclusively about mothers, this poem reminisces about the care and love a mother provides during childhood. It evokes nostalgia and gratitude.\n\n---\n\n### **7. \"Amma\" by Dushyant Kumar**\nThis poignant poem reflects on the struggles and sacrifices of a mother, emphasizing her resilience and unwavering love.\n\n---\n\nThese poems not only celebrate the role of a mother but also evoke deep emotions, making them timeless and relatable. You can find these works in various Hindi poetry collections or online sources for a closer reading.",
